        <details>
          <summary>Abstract</summary>
          <article class="has-text-justified p-2"> This study examined the effects of the adoption of International
            Public Sector Accounting
            Standards (IPSAS) on relevance of information in financial report of public sector in Ondo state.
            A well-structured questionnaire was used to obtain data from 184 Auditors drawn as sample
            from population of 211 Auditors working under the Office of Auditor General of Ondo state. The
            study made use of descriptive statistics and non-parametric test to analyse data gathered.
            Chart and percentages were descriptive statistics adopted while chi-squared test was the non-
            parametric test employed. Findings from the study elicited that IPSAS adoption has increased
            the relevance of information in financial report significantly, since the Chi-square test result
            displayed a Chi-Square value of 151.94 and p-value of 0.000 at 5% significant level. It was
            therefore concluded that adoption of IPSAS has improved the information relevance of financial
            reports of public sectors in Ondo State significantly.</article>
