        <details>
          <summary>Abstract</summary>
          <article class="has-text-justified p-2"> The aim of the study is to apply forensic investigative techniques to
            investigate financial
            disclosure of blue chip firms on the Nigeria Stock Exchange. This study apply forensic
            investigative techniques to investigate the financial disclosure of blue chip firms in the Nigeria
            Stock Exchange, a descriptive method and purposive sampling techniques was used for
            gathering data of the sixteen (16) firms selected and their annual report were examined for
            earning manipulations, material misstatements and financial distress using Beneish M- score,
            Dechow F- Score and Altman Z-score respectively. Based on the findings of this study, earnings
            manipulations, materials misstatements and risk of financial distress was found in few firms of
            the blue chips selected for the study. However, majority of the firms do not manipulate the
            earnings, have a normal risk of material misstatements and operate in safe zone of being
            financial distress/insolvent. The study, therefore recommended that, Deschow Model, Beneish
            Model, Altman Z- score and other investigative techniques should be inculcated into the courses
            offered in Nigeria tertiary institution expectially in accounting departments. The Models should
            also be introduced into the Nigeria Audit system as one of the recommended analytical Audit
            techniques to aid External Auditors perform the necessary substantive tests, so as to effectively
            curtail the rising incidence of fraud among corporate organizations in Nigeria.</article>
